    "Looking ahead, this adaptive strategy could be further enhanced through more sophisticated active-learning schemes. 51,52",
    "We have introduced a practical and efficient Distilled Multiple Time Step (DMTS) scheme tailored to machine-learned force fields, enabling significant acceleration of molecular dynamics simulations without compromising accuracy for both static and dynamical properties.",
    "Our approach, based on a RESPA-like scheme, couples a fast, distilled neural network 0 1 2 Protein RMSD (Å) STS DMTS Generic DMTS Active Learning 0.0 2.5 5.0 7.5 10.0 12.5 15.0 17.5 20.0 Time (ns) 0 1 2 3 Ligand DBC (Å) We achieve substantial speedups -up to 4 in mostly homogeneous systems (bulk water and solvated small molecules) and 2.92 in large protein-ligand complexes -while preserving key physical observables such as radial distribution functions, hydration free energies, diffusion coefficients, and protein-ligand structural properties.",
    "Note that this is a first estimation of the computational gains as the code has yet to be optimized further to handle the dual-level approach more efficiently.",
    "All in all, our approach allows to reach above 7 ns of simulation per day on a single A100 GPU for a realistic protein-ligand complex while preserving the ab initio-like accuracy of the FeNNix-Bio1(M) model."
